om"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Portal:Ashura"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-100 ns-subject page-Portal_Ashura rootpage-Portal_Ashura skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Portal:Ashura</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div id="portals-browsebar" class="hlist" style="text-align: center;">\n<dl>\n<dt><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Topics</a></dt>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Culture_and_the_arts" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Culture</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Geography_and_places" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Geography</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Health_and_fitness" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Health</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#History_and_events" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">History</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Mathematics_and_logic" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Mathematics</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Natural_and_physical_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Nature</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#People_and_self" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">People</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Philosophy_and_thinking" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Philosophy</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Religion_and_belief_systems" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Religion</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Society_and_social_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Society</a></dd>\n<dd><a href="/wiki/Portal:Contents/Portals#Technology_and_applied_sciences" title="Portal:Contents/Portals">Technology</a></dd>\n</dl>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:both; width:100%">\n<div style="position:relative; overflow:hidden; background:white; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaaaaa;">\n<div style="overflow-x:hidden; overflow:hidden; width:100%">\n<p><a href="/wiki/File:Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Portrait of Ashura.jpg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg/1150px-Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg" width="1150" height="194" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg/1725px-Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg/2300px-Portrait_of_Ashura.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3200" data-file-height="540" /></a></p>\n<div style="position:absolute; top:1em; left: 1em; padding:1em;">\n<div style="float: left; margin: 1px;">\n<table cellspacing="0" style="width: 350px; color:black; background: transparent;">\n<tr>\n<td style="width: 30px; height: 70px; background: #transparent; text-align: center; font-size: 23pt;"></td>\n<td style="/* insecure input */"><span style="font-size:123%;"><b>Welcome to the Ashura Portal</b><br /></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Intro&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Ashura"><big>Ashura</big></span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p>The <b>Ashura</b> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ar">\xd8\xb9\xd8\xa7\xd8\xb4\xd9\x88\xd8\xb1\xd8\xa7\xd8\xa1</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e <i><span title="ar ALA transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none">\xca\xbb\xc4\x80sh\xc5\xabr\xc4\x81\xe2\x80\x99&#160;</span></i><span style="margin-left:1px">,</span> <a href="/wiki/Varieties_of_Arabic" title="Varieties of Arabic">colloquially</a>: <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xca\x95a(\xcb\x90)\xcb\x88\xca\x83u\xcb\x90ra/</span>; <a href="/wiki/Urdu_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Urdu language">Urdu</a>: <span lang="ur" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ur">\xd8\xb9\xd8\xa7\xd8\xb4\xd9\x88\xd8\xb1\xd8\xa7</span>\xe2\x80\x8e; <a href="/wiki/Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" dir="rtl" xml:lang="fa">\xd8\xb9\xd8\xa7\xd8\xb4\xd9\x88\xd8\xb1\xd8\xa7</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xca\x95\xc9\x92\xcb\x90\xca\x83u\xcb\x90\xcb\x88\xc9\xbe\xc9\x92/</span>; <a href="/wiki/Turkish_language" title="Turkish language">Turkish</a>: <span lang="tr" xml:lang="tr"><i>A\xc5\x9fure G\xc3\xbcn\xc3\xbc</i></span><span style="margin-left:2.5px">)</span> is on the tenth day of <a href="/wiki/Muharram" title="Muharram">Muharram</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Islamic_calendar" title="Islamic calendar">Islamic calendar</a> and marks the climax of the <a href="/wiki/Remembrance_of_Muharram" class="mw-redirect" title="Remembrance of Muharram">Remembrance of Muharram</a>. <a href="/wiki/Shi%27a" class="mw-redirect" title="Shi\'a">Shi\'a</a> Muslims maintain that Ashura is a day of great sorrow due to the tragic events of Karbala. It is commemorated by <a href="/wiki/Shi%27a" class="mw-redirect" title="Shi\'a">Shi\'a</a> Muslims as a day of <a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">mourning for the martyrdom</a> of Husayn ibn Ali, the grandson of <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a> at the Battle of Karbala on 10 <a href="/wiki/Muharram" title="Muharram">Muharram</a> in the year 61 AH ( in <a href="/wiki/Tabular_Islamic_calendar" title="Tabular Islamic calendar">AHt</a>: October 10, 680 CE). The massacre of Husayn with small group of his companions and family members had great impact on the religious conscience of Muslims. Especially Shia Muslims have ever remembered it with sorrow and passion. Mourning for Husayn and his companions began almost immediately after the Battle of Karbala, by his survivor relatives and supporters.</p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="text-align:center; margin:0.25em auto 0.75em"><span class="noprint plainlinks purgelink"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura&amp;action=purge"><span title="Purge this page"><b>Show new selections</b></span></a></span></div>\n<div class="portal-column-left">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Selected_article/2&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_article">Selected article</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:left;margin-right:1em"><a href="/wiki/File:AschuraFestKarbala.jpg" class="image" title="Karbala at Arba\'een"><img alt="Karbala at Arba\'een" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/AschuraFestKarbala.jpg/100px-AschuraFestKarbala.jpg" width="100" height="70" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/AschuraFestKarbala.jpg/150px-AschuraFestKarbala.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/AschuraFestKarbala.jpg/200px-AschuraFestKarbala.jpg 2x" data-file-width="1353" data-file-height="951" /></a></div>\n<b>The Mourning of Muharram</b> marks the anniversary of the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Karbala" title="Battle of Karbala">Battle of Karbala</a> when Imam <a href="/wiki/Hussein_ibn_Ali" class="mw-redirect" title="Hussein ibn Ali">Hussein ibn Ali</a>, the grandson of <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a>, was killed by the forces of the second <a href="/wiki/Umayyad_Caliphate" title="Umayyad Caliphate">Umayyad caliph</a> <a href="/wiki/Yazid_I" title="Yazid I">Yazid I</a> at <a href="/wiki/Karbala" title="Karbala">Karbala</a>. Family members, accompanying <a href="/wiki/Hussein_ibn_Ali" class="mw-redirect" title="Hussein ibn Ali">Hussein ibn Ali</a>, were killed or subjected to humiliation. The commemoration of the event during yearly mourning season, from first of <a href="/wiki/Muharram" title="Muharram">Muharram</a> to twentieth of <a href="/wiki/Safar" title="Safar">Safar</a> with <a href="/wiki/Day_of_Ashura" class="mw-redirect" title="Day of Ashura">Ashura</a> comprising the focal date, serves to define <a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shia</a> communal identity. At present, Muharram Observances are carried out in countries with noteworthy <a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shia</a> population, including <a href="/wiki/Afghanistan" title="Afghanistan">Afghanistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Azerbaijan" title="Azerbaijan">Azerbaijan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a>, <a href="/wiki/Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a>, <a href="/wiki/Turkey" title="Turkey">Turkey</a>, <a href="/wiki/Pakistan" title="Pakistan">Pakistan</a>, <a href="/wiki/Lebanon" title="Lebanon">Lebanon</a>, <a href="/wiki/India" title="India">India</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Bahrain" title="Bahrain">Bahrain</a>.\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_article" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected article">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected_article&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected article (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_article" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected article">More articles...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Selected_biography/1&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_biography">Selected biography</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.2em"><a href="/wiki/File:Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg" class="image" title="The shrine of Husayn, as seen from the shrine of Abbas in Karbala, Karbala Governorate, Iraq"><img alt="The shrine of Husayn, as seen from the shrine of Abbas in Karbala, Karbala Governorate, Iraq" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg/150px-Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg" width="150" height="99" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg/225px-Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4f/Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg/300px-Kerbela_Hussein_Moschee.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2464" data-file-height="1632" /></a></div>\n<b><a href="/wiki/Husayn_ibn_%E2%80%98Al%C4%AB_ibn_Ab%C4%AB_T%C4%81lib" class="mw-redirect" title="Husayn ibn \xe2\x80\x98Al\xc4\xab ibn Ab\xc4\xab T\xc4\x81lib">Husayn ibn \xe2\x80\x98Al\xc4\xab ibn Ab\xc4\xab T\xc4\x81lib</a></b> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic_language" class="mw-redirect" title="Arabic language">Arabic</a>: <span lang="ar" dir="rtl" xml:lang="ar">\xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xad\xd8\xb3\xd9\x8a\xd9\x86 \xd8\xa8\xd9\x86 \xd8\xb9\xd9\x84\xd9\x8a \xd8\xa8\xd9\x86 \xd8\xa3\xd8\xa8\xd9\x8a \xd8\xb7\xd8\xa7\xd9\x84\xd8\xa8</span>\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e\xe2\x80\x8e; 08 January 626 AD \xe2\x80\x93 10 October 680 AD) (3rd / 4th <a href="/wiki/Sha%27aban" class="mw-redirect" title="Sha\'aban">Sha\'aban</a> 4 <a href="/wiki/Islamic_calendar" title="Islamic calendar">AH</a> \xe2\x80\x93 10th <a href="/wiki/Muharram" title="Muharram">Muharram</a> 61&#160;AH), sometimes spelled <b>Hussein</b>, was the son of <a href="/wiki/Ali" title="Ali">Ali ibn Abi \xe1\xb9\xacalib</a> (fourth <a href="/wiki/Rashidun" title="Rashidun">Rashidun Caliph</a> of <a href="/wiki/Sunni_Islam" title="Sunni Islam">Sunni Islam</a>, and first <a href="/wiki/Imamah_(Shia_doctrine)" title="Imamah (Shia doctrine)">Imam</a> of <a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shia Islam</a>) and <a href="/wiki/Fatimah" title="Fatimah">Fatimah Zahra</a> (daughter of <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a>) and the younger brother of <a href="/wiki/Hasan_ibn_Ali" title="Hasan ibn Ali">Hasan ibn Ali</a>. Husayn is an important figure in <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a>, as he is a member of the <a href="/wiki/Ahl_al-Bayt" title="Ahl al-Bayt">Ahl al-Bayt</a> (the household of Muhammad) and <a href="/wiki/Ahl_al-Kisa" title="Ahl al-Kisa">Ahl al-Kisa</a>, as well as being the third Shia Imam.Husayn is highly regarded by <a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shiite Muslims</a> because he refused to pledge allegiance to <a href="/wiki/Yazid_I" title="Yazid I">Yazid I</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Umayyad_Caliphate" title="Umayyad Caliphate">Umayyad</a> <a href="/wiki/Caliph" class="mw-redirect" title="Caliph">caliph</a> because he considered the rule of the <a href="/wiki/Umayyads" class="mw-redirect" title="Umayyads">Umayyads</a> unjust. As a consequence, he left Medina, his home town, and traveled to <a href="/wiki/Mecca" title="Mecca">Mecca</a>. At Karbala his caravan was intercepted by <a href="/wiki/Yazid_I" title="Yazid I">Yazid I</a>\'s army. He was killed and beheaded in the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Karbala" title="Battle of Karbala">Battle of Karbala</a> in 680 (61 AH) by <a href="/wiki/Shimr_Ibn_Thil-Jawshan" class="mw-redirect" title="Shimr Ibn Thil-Jawshan">Shimr Ibn Thil-Jawshan</a>, along with most of his family and companions. The annual memorial for him, his family, his children and his companions is called <i><a href="/wiki/Day_of_Ashura" class="mw-redirect" title="Day of Ashura">Ashura</a></i> (tenth day of Muharram) and is a <a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">day of mourning</a> for <a href="/wiki/Shia_Islam" title="Shia Islam">Shiite Muslims</a>. The killings at Karbala fueled the later Shiite movements. Anger at Husayn\'s death was turned into a rallying cry that helped undermine and ultimately overthrow the <a href="/wiki/Umayyad_Caliphate" title="Umayyad Caliphate">Umayyad Caliphate</a>.\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_biography" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected biography">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:0px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Husayn_ibn_Ali" title="Husayn ibn Ali">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected_biography&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected biography (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_biography" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected biography">More biographies...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/News&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="In_the_news">In the news</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<p><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/News&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/News (page does not exist)">Portal:Ashura/News</a></p>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Current_events&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/Current events (page does not exist)">More current events...</a><br />\n<a href="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki/Portal:Ashura" class="extiw" title="wikinews:Portal:Ashura">Current events</a> on <a href="https://en.wikinews.org/wiki/en" class="extiw" title="wikinews:en">Wikinews</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="portal-column-right">\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Selected_picture/2&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Selected_picture">Selected picture</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div class="center">\n<div class="floatnone"><a href="/wiki/File:Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_(66).jpg" class="image" title="Mourning of Muharram in cities and villages of Iran"><img alt="Mourning of Muharram in cities and villages of Iran" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/375px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg" width="375" height="237" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/563px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/02/Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg/750px-Mourning_of_Muharram_in_cities_and_villages_of_Iran-342_16_%2866%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="4608" data-file-height="2910" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<center><small>Credit: Payam Moein</small></center>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>As a custom for <a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">Mourning of Muharram</a>, people in <a href="/wiki/Iran" title="Iran">Iran</a> perform <a href="/wiki/Husayn_ibn_Ali" title="Husayn ibn Ali">Husayn ibn Ali</a>\'s <a href="/wiki/Funeral" title="Funeral">funeral</a> by carrying a huge wooden structure called "Nakhl", which is usually carried by several hundred men.</p>\n<table class="noprint" width="100%" border="0" style="padding: 0; margin: 0; background-color:transparent">\n<tr>\n<td width="33%">\n<div style="text-align:left;"><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_picture" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected picture">...Archive/Nominations</a></b></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div style="text-align:right;margin-right:10px;margin-bottom:4px;">\n<p><b><a href="/wiki/Muharram" title="Muharram">More...</a></b></p>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected_picture&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/Nominate/Selected picture (page does not exist)">Suggest</a> \xe2\x80\xa2 <a href="/wiki/Portal:Ashura/Selected_picture" title="Portal:Ashura/Selected picture">More pictures...</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;margin-bottom:.1em;font-size:80%; color: white"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Did_you_know&amp;action=edit"><span style="color: white">edit</span></a>&#160;&#160;</div>\n<h2 style="font-family:sans-serif; font-size:100%; font-weight:bold; border: none; margin: 0; padding:0; padding-bottom:.1em; color:white;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Did_you_know.3F">Did you know?</span></h2>\n</div>\n<div style="border: 1px solid #008000; border-top-width: 1px; vertical-align: top;background: #f9f9ff;opacity: 1; color: black; text-align: left; margin: 0 0 10px; padding: 1em;padding-top: .3em;">\n<div style="float:right;margin-left:0.5em;">\n<p><a href="/wiki/File:Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain,_2012.jpg" class="image" title="Muharram procession in Bahrain"><img alt="Muharram procession in Bahrain" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg/100px-Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg" width="100" height="81" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg/150px-Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8e/Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg/200px-Muharram_procession_in_Bahrain%2C_2012.jpg 2x" data-file-width="468" data-file-height="378" /></a></p>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li>...that the <b><a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">Mourning of Muharram</a></b>, observed by <a href="/wiki/Shi%27a" class="mw-redirect" title="Shi\'a">Shi\'a</a> <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Muslims</a>, commemorates the anniversary of the death of <a href="/wiki/Imam" title="Imam">Imam</a> <a href="/wiki/Husayn_ibn_Ali" title="Husayn ibn Ali">Husayn ibn Ali</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Karbala" title="Battle of Karbala">Battle of Karbala</a> in <a href="/wiki/680" title="680">680</a>?</li>\n<li>...that due to the large number of pilgrims who visit <b><a href="/wiki/Muharram_in_Bahrain" title="Muharram in Bahrain">Bahrain during Muharram</a></b> <i>(<a href="/wiki/Mourning_of_Muharram" title="Mourning of Muharram">Muharram procession</a> pictured)</i>, the country has been referred to as the "<a href="/wiki/Karbala" title="Karbala">Karbala</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Persian_Gulf" title="Persian Gulf">Gulf</a>"?</li>\n<li>...that <i>Muslim ibn Awsaja al-Asadi</i> was a companion of Muhammad prophet who participated at in <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_Karbala" title="Battle of Karbala">Battle of Karbala</a> as a companion of Hussain ibn Ali?</li>\n<li>...that <i>Wahhab ibn Abdullah al-Kalbi</i> was <a href="/wiki/Christian" title="Christian">Christian</a> companion of <a href="/wiki/Hussain_ibn_Ali" class="mw-redirect" title="Hussain ibn Ali">Hussain ibn Ali</a> who was killed in <a href="/wiki/Battle_of_karbala" class="mw-redirect" title="Battle of karbala">battle of karbala</a>?</li>\n</ul>\n<div class="noprint" style="margin:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; padding:0.3em 0.2em 0.2em 0.3em; text-align:right;"><b><a href="/w/index.php?title=Portal:Ashura/Did_you_know/archive&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Portal:Ashura/Did you know/archive (page does not exist)">Archive</a> \xe2\x80\x93 <a href="/wiki/Help:Starting_a_new_page" class="mw-redirect" title="Help:Starting a new page">Start a new article</a></b></div>\n<div style="clear:both;"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div style="clear:both; width:100%">\n<p><br /></p>\n<div style="clear: both; border: solid #008000; border-width: 1px 1px 0; background: black; color: white; padding: .1em;padding-top: .1em;padding-left: .1em;padding-right: .1em;padding-bottom: .1em;text-align: center;font-family: sans-serif;font-size:100%;margin-bottom: 0px;">\n<div class="plainlinks" style="float:right;ma